ful and elegant analysis of the responsibility of writing, Proust among the Nations makes the case for literature as a unique resource for understanding political struggle and gives us new ways to think creatively about the violence in the Middle East.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aArab-Israeli conflictxLiterature and the conflict. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  aenglish major, academic, scholarly, research, analysis, close reading, analyzed, critical, critique, author, well known, famous, middle east, dreyfus, psychoanalysis, interdisciplinary, literature, literary, political, politics, israel palestine, conflict, crisis, western, problem, dialogue, freud, philosophical, writer, artist, filmmaker, memory, identity, culture, cultural, international, global, interpretation.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z97831106353860 cprintz978022672578940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226725802423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226725802/original  a978-3-11-063538-6  University of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles